  "chapter": {
    "number": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Song of the Vineyard"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will sing for my beloved a song of his vineyard:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "My beloved had a vineyard",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on a very fertile hill.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He dug it up and cleared the stones",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and planted the finest vines.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He built a watchtower in the middle",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and dug out a winepress as well.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "He waited for the vineyard to yield good grapes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the fruit it produced was sour!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“And now, O dwellers of Jerusalem",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and men of Judah,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I exhort you to judge",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "between Me and My vineyard.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What more could I have done for My vineyard",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than I already did for it?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Why, when I expected sweet grapes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "did it bring forth sour fruit?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Now I will tell you what I am about to do to My vineyard:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "I will take away its hedge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and it will be consumed;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will tear down its wall,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and it will be trampled.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will make it a wasteland,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "neither pruned nor cultivated,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and thorns and briers will grow up.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will command the clouds",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that rain shall not fall on it.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the vineyard of the LORD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is the house of Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the men of Judah",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are the plant of His delight.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He looked for justice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but saw bloodshed;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but heard a cry of distress.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Woes to the Wicked"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to you who add house to house",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and join field to field",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "until no place is left",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you live alone in the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I heard the LORD of Hosts declare:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Surely many houses will become desolate,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "great mansions left unoccupied.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For ten acres of vineyard",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will yield but a bath of wine,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2520
          },
          {
            "text": "and a homer of seed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only an ephah of grain.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2521
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those who rise early in the morning",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in pursuit of strong drink,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who linger into the evening,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to be inflamed by wine.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "At their feasts are the lyre and harp,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "tambourines and flutes and wine.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They disregard the actions of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and fail to see the work of His hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore My people will go into exile",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for their lack of understanding;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their dignitaries are starving",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their masses are parched with thirst.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore Sheol enlarges its throat",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and opens wide its enormous jaws,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and down go Zion’s nobles and masses,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her revelers and carousers!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So mankind will be brought low, and each man humbled;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the arrogant will lower their eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the LORD of Hosts will be exalted by His justice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the holy God will show Himself holy in righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lambs will graze as in their own pastures,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and strangers",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2522
          },
          {
            "text": "will feed in the ruins of the wealthy.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those who draw iniquity with cords of deceit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pull sin along with cart ropes,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to those who say, “Let Him hurry and hasten His work",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may see it!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let the plan of the Holy One of Israel come",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may know it!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those who call evil good",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and good evil,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who turn darkness to light",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and light to darkness,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who replace bitter with sweet",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sweet with bitter.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those who are wise in their own eyes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and clever in their own sight.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to those who are heroes in drinking wine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and champions in mixing beer,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who acquit the guilty for a bribe",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and deprive the innocent of justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, as a tongue of fire consumes the straw,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and as dry grass shrivels in the flame,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so their roots will decay",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their blossoms will blow away like dust;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for they have rejected the instruction of the LORD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and despised the word of the Holy One of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore the anger of the LORD burns against His people;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His hand is raised against them to strike them down.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The mountains quake,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the corpses lay like refuse in the streets.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Despite all this, His anger is not turned away;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His hand is still upraised.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He lifts a banner for the distant nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and whistles for those at the ends of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Behold—how speedily and swiftly they come!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "None of them grows weary or stumbles;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no one slumbers or sleeps.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "No belt is loose",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and no sandal strap is broken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their arrows are sharpened,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all their bows are strung.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The hooves of their horses are like flint;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their chariot wheels are like a whirlwind.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their roaring is like that of a lion;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they roar like young lions.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They growl and seize their prey;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they carry it away from deliverance.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day they will roar over it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like the roaring of the sea.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "If one looks over the land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he will see darkness and distress;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even the light will be obscured by clouds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2520,
        "caller": "+",
